# Pricing Calculator Conventions

## Stack and structure

- **Next.js 14** (App Router), **React**, **TypeScript**, **Tailwind CSS**
- **Forms**: `react-hook-form` with **zod** schema; resolver in `app/page.tsx`
- **Pricing**: All calculation logic in `lib/pricing.ts`; tunable values in `config/pricing.json`
- **Types**: `WindowEntry` and `LeadInfo` in `lib/types.ts`; `WindowInput`, `ProjectEstimate` in `lib/pricing.ts`

## Key flows

- **Estimate**: `app/page.tsx` maps form `windows` to `WindowInput[]` and calls `computeProjectEstimate(windows, projectType)`. Add new window fields to: `lib/types.ts` (`WindowEntry`), `app/page.tsx` (schema + default in `createDefaultWindow` + estimate/submit mapping), and optionally `lib/pricing.ts` (`WindowInput` and logic).
- **Special equipment (15 ft)**: When any window has `topAbove15Feet`, `computeProjectEstimate` sets `specialEquipmentRequired: true` and `canShowPriceRange: false`. `Summary.tsx` shows prices as N/A and greyed out in that case; the estimated range block is hidden.

## Pricing config

- **`config/pricing.json`**: `filmTypes`, `perSqftAdders` (e.g. woodFrame, skylight, existingFilmRemovalMin/Max), `flatAdders` (e.g. stairwellPerWindow), `minimumProjectInvestment`, `roundToNearest`, `njTaxRate`, `commercialPricePerSqftAdder`. Add new adders here and read them in `lib/pricing.ts` via `getPricingConfig()`.

## UI

- **WindowForm**: Per-window fields and checkboxes (e.g. “Located above stairs”, “Top of frame exceeds 15 ft”, “Existing film removal required”). Checkbox section uses a 2-column layout with “Check all that apply” in the left column and checkboxes in the right.
- **Summary**: Displays line items, subtotal, minimum, tax, total; when `specialEquipmentRequired`, same layout but amounts show “N/A” and section is greyed out. Always show the “Estimate summary” heading.

## Testing

- Unit tests for pricing live in `__tests__/lib/pricing.test.ts`. Use `WindowInput` from `lib/pricing.ts` for test fixtures (e.g. `baseWindow`).

